dismissalText.commentary: Jonny Bairstow c Munsey b Berrington 105 (59b 12x4 6x6) SR: 177.96

dismissalComment.html: slogged towards long-off... the Bairstow express has gone off the tracks! Munsey holds a steepler, running around the rope before steadying himself to complete the dismissal. Berrington's medium-pace does the trick, Scotland needed that

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Evans b Berrington 52 (56b 3x4 3x6) SR: 92.85

dismissalComment.html: another one, Hales slaps straight to point! Two in two balls for Scotland and this game has come alive again! Hales slumps on his bat, that was basically a wide long hop, but he has picked out Evans, who takes the catch to follow up his breakthrough with the ball

dismissalText.commentary: Mark Wood lbw b Sharif 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: SCOTLAND HAVE DONE IT A brilliant yorker traps Wood in front and the ground erupts. What a delivery, late inswing, takes Wood on the boot. Incredible scenes.

headshotImage.caption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mark Wood lbw b Sharif 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

commentTextItems.html: SCOTLAND HAVE DONE IT A brilliant yorker traps Wood in front and the ground erupts. What a delivery, late inswing, takes Wood on the boot. Incredible scenes.

commentPostTextItems.html: We have a pitch invasion from the delighted hope supporters. After an incredible day Scotland have won by six runs to beat England for the first time. One of the great days in Scotland's sporting history. A now a rendition of Flower of Scotland starts. Hugs all round in the Scotland camp. A thrilling match played on a superb batting pitch, but it was Scotland's nerve and guts with the ball - and in the field - which ultimately won them the game after Calum MacLeod's magnificent century earlier in the day. After Jonny Bairstow's barnstorming century, England will feel they should have chased those down but they played a full ill-judged shots at times - and there was some poor running as well. That, though, can all wait. This is Scotland's day
AM Ghouri: "what a last 10 or 12 hours for cricket. bangla women won the asia cup, WI won the test match and now Scotland wins against England. so happy"

Safyaan Sharif "Incredible effort from the lads, they've just proven once again that they are capable of playing at this standard, and they did really well throughout the innings. Up top, it was tough in the second half but we manged to pull things back and did the job so really... I'm lost for words, I don't know what to say.

"I just knew if I bowl the right line and hit my yorker, it's going to tail, and luckily once again I managed to hit that yorker and got that wicket which was an absolutely great feeling to get over the line."

Kyle Coetzer "A hugely special day for us, our coach said we should make history and we've done that. Credit to Calum, that outstanding knock, and what an occasion it was. In the first Powerplay, wherever we moved the field [Bairstow] hit it somewhere else and I was basically hoping he would mishit one. I'm extremely proud, but it is a trait we are getting very good. The last couple of years we have been very good with the ball. 371 plays 365 is an outstanding. The bowlers found it hard, but great to be on this side of the fence."
Scotland's players doing a lap of honour and signing autographs. Wonderful scenes on a sunny evening in Edinburgh.

Eoin Morgan "I thought they played close to their best cricket and we didn't. Full credit to Scotland, bringing your best game for a one-off game is hard to do. Don't think it's the worst thing for us...a couple of mistakes. We got rewards for our shots which brought us close, but not close enough. I think we were a little bit rusty, missed our lines a bit, we only got together yesterday. I think we'll be better for the run out. The level of expectation around the team has been quite high for a while, so we've managed to deal with that pretty well. If it is a problem it's something we'll have to address but don't think it is. It's a difficult summer ahead for us, but it was a good run out. I don't think we are far away, against a strong Australia they'll be extremely difficult to beat."

We'll leave the immediate post-match reaction there. But we'll have plenty more on the site over the next few hours and tomorrow. What a day for Scotland. They'll enjoy tonight! From Gnasher and Alan it's goodbye and we'll see you for the first match against Australia on Wednesday.

commentTextItems.html: full ball, heaved in the air through midwicket, again wide of long-on but they won't be taking on Leask's arm this time
low full toss on the pads, could have been costly but it's just clipped to deep square
full and straight, firmly down the ground to long-off...England can't take any risks now

commentPostTextItems.html: Another chat between captain and bowler. One ball will do it

dismissalText.commentary: Adil Rashid run out (Leask/Sharif) 5 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 62.5

commentPreTextItems.html: It will be Sharif with the penultimate over. Milan: "It's 11:23 in Nepal and I'm watching this match just to see Scotland winning this one , come on Scotland, show the power of associate nation"

commentTextItems.html: Rashid is gone here! What drama! Coming back for the second. Plunkett swung this down the ground, just wide of long-on, and they chanced the second. Strong throw from the deep by Leask and a good gather at the stumps

desperation all round! Plunkett swings at a yorker, squeezes it into the leg side, sets off for a scampered run, Sole bounds across from his follow through, dives, collects and almost hits at the non-striker's end. Would have been tight

short outside off, Rashid goes over cover, didn't find the middle and plops in front of the sweeper

commentPreTextItems.html: Sole is brought back for the 48th over. Plenty of conversations going on. From Peter: "The crowd sitting outside the Grange pavilion is singing 'Flower of Scotland.' Goosebumps. They want Scotland to pull it off badly."

commentTextItems.html: back of a length, swings in quite significantly, pushed into the off side
well bowled, some late inswing on that yorker, pushed down the ground to long-off. Scotland have found some reverse late on

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Cross c †Billings b Plunkett 48 (39b 10x4 0x6) SR: 123.07

dismissalComment.html: Plunkett gets him, nicked to the keeper! Some relief from England, silencing both openers after an impressive salvo... Cross misses out on fifty, he was just trying to glide that to third man, I think, but ended up steering a simple catch to Billings

headshotImage.caption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Richie Berrington c Root b Plunkett 39 (54b 3x4 1x6) SR: 72.22

dismissalComment.html: good catch from Root as he runs back from mid-off...Berrington looking to go down the ground, it's just short of a good length and a cross-seam delivery, gets too far underneath it

headshotImage.caption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Adil Rashid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Munsey c Wood b Rashid 55 (51b 7x4 1x6) SR: 107.84

dismissalComment.html: pushed through, the sweep it top-edged - well taken running towards short fine leg! Munsey is a goner, but he has played a perfect hand. Second wicket for Rashid, gives England an opening

dismissalText.commentary: Dylan Budge b Wood 11 (9b 1x4 0x6) SR: 122.22

dismissalComment.html: timber! Off stump out of the ground... That's a good death-overs delivery, full and quick and sending Budge back as he misses with a big old yahoo

headshotImage.longCaption: Jason Roy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Roy c & b Watt 34 (32b 3x4 0x6) SR: 106.25

dismissalComment.html: breakthrough! Spin does the trick. Roy pushes a length ball back for a simple return catch. May have just held in the surface. Good bowling, good captaincy

headshotImage.caption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonny Bairstow player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jonny Bairstow c Munsey b Berrington 105 (59b 12x4 6x6) SR: 177.96

dismissalComment.html: slogged towards long-off... the Bairstow express has gone off the tracks! Munsey holds a steepler, running around the rope before steadying himself to complete the dismissal. Berrington's medium-pace does the trick, Scotland needed that

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Evans b Berrington 52 (56b 3x4 3x6) SR: 92.85

dismissalComment.html: another one, Hales slaps straight to point! Two in two balls for Scotland and this game has come alive again! Hales slumps on his bat, that was basically a wide long hop, but he has picked out Evans, who takes the catch to follow up his breakthrough with the ball

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root run out (Watt/Leask) 29 (25b 3x4 1x6) SR: 116

dismissalComment.html: dragged down, Root swivels to pulls, sends it off the bottom edge to short fine leg... but what's this, Hales has called for the run and Root is struggling desperately to get to the other end! Leask collects the throw and breaks the stumps and Root looks like he knows he's gone, here! Yes, out by a yard, England lose another in rather needless circumstances

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Coetzer b Evans 20 (15b 1x4 1x6) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: looped off the hip, into the leg side, Coetzer takes an excellent running catch! Well, there's a wicket, just what Scotland needed! Evans does it, got this to skip up from back of a length and Morgan spliced it in front of midwicket - a sharp chance, but well taken with both hands above his head

headshotImage.caption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sam Billings player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sam Billings c Coetzer b Watt 12 (14b 1x4 0x6) SR: 85.71

dismissalComment.html: low full toss, straight to short midwicket! So Billings can't take his chance, and Scotland favourites now. he can't believe it, ball was there for hitting, but he just picked out the man

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali c Munsey b Watt 46 (33b 3x4 3x6) SR: 139.39

dismissalComment.html: he's found long-on! There's a twist in this game yet...he tries to clean long-on, but doesn't find the middle. He also had to fetch it from outside off. Munsey settles under it

dismissalComment.html: and another! Scotland surging. Another short ball, this time slightly further outside off, Willey gets a top edge as he pulls

headshotImage.longCaption: Liam Plunkett player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Adil Rashid run out (Leask/Sharif) 5 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: Rashid is gone here! What drama! Coming back for the second. Plunkett swung this down the ground, just wide of long-on, and they chanced the second. Strong throw from the deep by Leask and a good gather at the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Mark Wood lbw b Sharif 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: SCOTLAND HAVE DONE IT A brilliant yorker traps Wood in front and the ground erupts. What a delivery, late inswing, takes Wood on the boot. Incredible scenes.
